4.4 Violation classes (reporting)
"violation_classes": {
  "BENEFIC_MALEFIC_FRAMING": {
    "severity": "blocking",
    "description": "Uses good/bad or lucky/unlucky framing for aspects."
  },
  "ALARMIST_ASPECT_LANGUAGE": {
    "severity": "blocking",
    "description": "Uses fear-based or catastrophic language about an aspect."
  },
  "ASPECT_AS_FATE": {
    "severity": "blocking",
    "description": "Treats an aspect as determining outcomes rather than describing interaction."
  }
}


5. Enforcement rules
Interpreter must:
Use core_dynamic + system_model as the basis for meaning
Avoid any forbidden framing
Allow multiple frames in bundles (not single “square = bad”)
QA must:
Scan for forbidden framings globally
Flag any aspect language not aligned with this file
